rComments: I remember during my first year he gave us a mid term that was fourth year level and then acted surprised when the class average was under 50%. The make up test was the level of difficulty a first year student should have expected to see in a first year class. Other than that, he was tolerable.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I really liked him, he was great help, and there was an issues with my google maps assignment and he took the time to meet me after the exam and it ended up being blackboards fault not mine, he is very caring and understanding

This is by far the best prof. at utm, the course work was great, use of powerpoint kept the class interesting, the tests had a variety, maps(those were awesome), mc, essay. the 10 page paper for the midterm he offered one on one help and notes to improve and make it even better, overall a really good experience and highly recommended!

His lectures are really detailed and his tests focus on small pointless details instead of the main points. The videos and his lectures are extremly important. He is also a great professor to talk to outside of class, he's really nice and he does truely care about his students. Great experience.

As a former student I can honestly say he was one of my favorite profs. I took classics as an elective to add variety to my courses in commerce and absolutely loved it! I thought his classes were interesting, fun and challenging - but I guess to enjoy his lectures, you have to be one of those people who actually like the challenge.
Cool teacher to talk to aside from the lecture, but class is extremely boring and you might fall asleep. He is rude to students who leave class while in the lecture, so dont do it.

Went into the class very excited, left in the mood to never recommend classics. Ever. To anyone attending while this guy is still working. very dry, very poor attitude towards student/teacher relationships in general.
course is really dry, and the lecture material is lame.  powerpoints are pointless and not helpful and the lectures are boring.

He's a nice guy, a funny guy, but the course sucks. Thought it was about ancient civilization but its almost completely about archeology. Throws too much information at a time. Course is based on map quizzes (memorize 150 things literally on a map) and Google Earth assignment (kinda lame). Talks really fast and expects too much.
Awesome.

He seems like a nice enough guy,but didn't expected to learn so much about archaeology. boring-ness i give a 3/5 xp. too much archaeology! Map Quizzes; the best- easy! Reading; no textbook, but articles are online- articles not my type of reading, cant get anything out of it really. Midterms/Exams; fairly okay, not hard as hell but doable
great teacher, available to meet outside class/office times. will go the extra mile to help any student achieve.

I thought the class was going to be a little more focused on the philosophical ideals of the ancient civilizations, but rather he made it simply on archaeology. There were weekly quizes based on the readings. The exam was so hard and had little to do with the course material.
Awesome as a person, but he throws too much information at once

I took his course a couple years ago and the average was a D+. I took it as an elective and maybe that's why I found it boring. I only went to a few classes throughout the whole term. His tests had  matching, map labelling, MC, essay, definitions, etc. I didn't do too badly though, ended up with a B+.

Covered a lot of course material in such a short time - not sure if it was his fault or not (I think in general it is too much topic to cover in a single term). His tests/exams are hard, but classes are pretty interesting. He uses powerpoint for his lectures, which is always helpful. Be prepared to study and keep up with readings.
Hard midterm, don't take it as an elective. He likes to read his lectures and has endless slides of detailed pictures of architecture that you're not tested on. Very boring.
Good teacher, but the material he tought sucked, and the final exam had NOTHING to do with the corse material

i found he taught the class too much like art-history. i would have preferred more on myths and social life of greek and roman times, then all about architecture. lots of reading in this course. very nice guy, willing to help if you ask for it. uses lots of visuals on powerpoint. taught alot on architecture, temple layouts,etc.

This prof. is an excellent, understanding teacher. He will go to great extremes to help students out. This class is very interesting and is never boring. His slides and lectures are amazing. VERY EXCELLENT!
His keen sense of humor confuses me sometimes - that's just his way I guess.  Stimulating topics covered.
He is the best prof I have, he has made me even more interested in the class and makes me want to go although its at 9am lol
